This edition of the LV Trainers teams smooth calf leather with grained calf leather embossed with Louis Vuitton's signature Monogram pattern. Title: Versace Chain Reaction sneakers
Body (HTML):
Versace

Chain Reaction sneakers

Legendary designer and founder Gianni Versace’s groundbreaking vision helped to reshape the fashion industry and secured the brand’s place as a symbol of glamour, decadence and luxury. These black leather paneled Chain Reaction sneakers from Versace SS19 feature a round toe, mesh panels, a lace-up front fastening, a logo patch at the tongue, a branded insole, a padded ankle, branded heel counter, a rubber sole, a signature Greek Key panel to the front and a pull tab at the tongue and heel.

Made in Italy

Title: Jordan x Travis Scott Air Jordan 1 Low sneakers
Body (HTML):
Jordan

x Travis Scott Air Jordan 1 Low sneakers

Imported

Highlights

Supplied by a premier sneaker marketplace dealing with unworn, already sold out, in demand rarities. Each product is rigorously inspected by experienced experts guaranteeing authenticity. The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Low is the low-top version of the world famous rapper’s Jordan 1 collaboration. Following the standard high-top Jordan 1 from spring 2019, this Jordan 1 Low by Travis Scott released in July in very limited quantities and achieved the same hype and coveted status as the first design. Scott once again displayed his affinity for earthy tones while also utilizing the same backwards Swoosh design as the initial high-top. The upper is constructed in premium nubuck with black and brown tones, while the large reversed Swoosh contrasts in white leather. Red highlights are found on the tongue tags and embroidered heel logos, while a Sail midsole completes the clean design.

Body (HTML):
Jordan

Following his popular Nike Air Force 1 collaboration with mix-and-match Swooshes, Travis Scott continued his reign as one of the sneaker world's hottest collaborators in 2018 with the Air Jordan 4 'Cactus Jack'. The bright blue nubuck construction with black and red accents takes inspiration from the team colors of the now defunct Houston Oilers football team, a reference to the rapper's Texas roots. Speckled detailing and Scott's 'Cactus Jack' logo on the left heel tab add more personal touches to the shoe.

Title: Air Jordan 4 Metallic Gold
Body (HTML):
The Women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Metallic Gold’ has a smooth leather upper with a subtle off-white finish and metallic gold eyelets for a regal look. These shoes have a breathable quarter panel netting and a debossed Jumpman logo on the tongue. The prominent molded heel tab backs a plush collar. Underneath, a soft midsole reveals an Air-sole heel unit for soft cushioning. The classic herringbone rubber outsole provides traction and optimal grip.

SKU: AQ9129 170
Colorway: Sail/Metallic Gold/Black
Release Date: 3/9/24

Title: Rayssa Leal X Dunk Low SB
Body (HTML):
The Rayssa Leal x Nike Dunk Low SB 'Deep Royal Vivid Purple' brings mismatched blue and fuchsia Swooshes that highlight the white leather upper, along with patterned grey suede overlays. The Brazilian skateboarder's logo adorns the heel, while three multicolored lace jewels showcase digital smiley faces for a custom look. The smiley faces are once again embossed in a monogram pattern throughout each quarter panel. A gum rubber outsole provides solid traction underfoot.

SKU: FZ5251 001
Colorway: Pure Platinum/Deep Royal Blue/Vivid Purple/White/Gum Yellow

Title: Fragment Design x Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low
Body (HTML): The Fragment Design x Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low released as part of a collaboration with the Houston rapper and Japanese imprint. Featuring a colorway that recalls previous fragment design collaborations, the shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, overlaid by black and royal blue and complemented by inverted Swoosh branding on the lateral side. The heel patch of the left shoe includes Cactus Jack branding and a smiley face logo, while fragment's lightning bolt marks the right shoe. Underfoot, a two-tone rubber cupsole anchors the design.

Title: Jordan Jumpman Jack TR 'Sail'
Body (HTML): An earthy take on Travis Scott's debut signature shoes, the Jordan Jumpman Jack TR 'Sail' have a dark brown canvas upper with off-white leather overlays and a beige backward Swoosh. These kicks have an adjustable midfoot strap, paired with regular shoelaces and contrasting red accents on the Jumpman tongue logo. Scott's Cactus Jack face logo is embossed on the back heel, while a white foam midsole and a gum rubber outsole anchor the look.

Title: Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Vivid Sulfur'
Body (HTML): The Women's Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Vivid Sulfur' brings some of the signature AJ4 details like a breathable side netting and support wings for midfoot support. The smooth white leather upper gets contrasting yellow accents on the eyelets, lining, and Jumpman logos on the tongue and back tab. These shoes have a two-tone midsole, equipped with an exposed Air-sole unit inside the heel.

Title: Travis Scott X Jordan Jumpman Jack University Red
Body (HTML): Done in an official color scheme listed as Sail/University Red-Black-Muslin, this new Travis Scott model features a Black mesh construction on the upper which is noted on the side panels and toes along with Sail on the tumbled leather overlays and the suede detailing on the heels. Additional standout details include a midfoot branded strap, red Jumpman branding on the tongues, the Cactus Jack smiley face on the heels, the now iconic reverse Swoosh in a University Red color on the lateral side panel, and “Jack” branding on the Muslin rubber outsoles.

Title: Air Jordan 4 Retro “ Military Blue 2024"
Body (HTML): This is the 2006 edition of the ' Military Blue ' Air Jordan 4 Retro – the first time since its original launch in 1989 that the OG colorway struck shops. The mid-top sports a straightforward two-tone design with a Jumpman logo on the heel rather than the initial Nike Air branding. Hits of contrasting Military Blue on the heel, eyelets, quarter panel and midsole accentuate a white leather upper.

Title: Jordan 3 X J Balvin Rio
Body (HTML):
This J Balvin x Air Jordan 3 is named after his son, Rio, who was born in June 2021. Our first look shows that the J Balvin x Air Jordan 3 Rio comes dressed in a Black, Solar Flare, and Total Crimson Abyss color scheme. Design details include a Black leather base, Grey elephant print overlays on the toe and heels, a gradient midsole and outsole, and translucent heel tabs housing J Balvin’s smiley logo on the right heel and Nike Air branding on the left heel. Design details paying tribute to J Balvin’s son, Rio will also be present, but have yet to be unveiled.
